<exercise checkit-seed="0009" checkit-slug="AI2" checkit-title="Arc Length">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Consider the curve <m>y=-x^{5}</m> defined on <m>[2, 4]</m>.
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Estimate the arclength of this curve with <m>5</m> line segments with <m>\Delta x = 0.4</m>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Find an integral that computes the arclength of this curve.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <me>
               \begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|c|}
              \hline
              x_i
              &amp;
              x_{i+1}
              &amp;
              f(x_{i})
              &amp;
              f(x_{i+1})
              &amp;
              \text{Length of segment}          
              \\
              \hline
               2
              &amp; 
               2.4
              &amp;
               -32.0
              &amp; 
               -79.6262
              &amp;
               47.6279         
                  \\
               2.4
              &amp; 
               2.8
              &amp;
               -79.6262
              &amp; 
               -172.1037
              &amp;
               92.4783         
                  \\
               2.8
              &amp; 
               3.1999999999999997
              &amp;
               -172.1037
              &amp; 
               -335.5443
              &amp;
               163.4411         
                  \\
               3.2
              &amp; 
               3.6
              &amp;
               -335.5443
              &amp; 
               -604.6618
              &amp;
               269.1177         
                  \\
               3.6
              &amp; 
               4.0
              &amp;
               -604.6618
              &amp; 
               -1024.0
              &amp;
               419.3384         
                  \\
              
              \hline
              \end{array}
          </me>
              The estimated length of this curve is 992.0033999999999.      
                </li>
                <li>
                    The arclength is computed via <me>\int_{ 2 }^{ 4 }\sqrt{1+ \left(-5 \, x^{4}\right)^2}dx.</me> 
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
